label.value: Sachet Container

value.value: Container consisting of two surfaces made of flexible material to be closed only by sealing or folding over. The contents are intended for single use.

label.value: WLHR/Le Mouse
Scarifier Device

value.value: Device for scratching the skin.

label.value: Screw Cap Device

value.value: Hollow cylindrical object with screw thread, meant to close a container.

label.value: Sealant Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid, more or less viscous, sterile preparation intended for use as tissue glue.

label.value: Sealant Matrix Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of a pliable piece of material impregnated or coated with a sealant or with a powder that forms a sealant after contact with an appropriate fluid (e.g. blood). It may act as a hemostatic agent and/or tissue glue. The matrix may itself form part of the seal, and is usually absorbed by the body over time.

label.value: Sealant Powder Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be applied directly onto the intended site (e.g. a lesion) to form a hemostatic agent and/or tissue glue after contact with an appropriate fluid (e.g. blood).

label.value: Semi-solid

value.value: A state of matter consisting of molecules in a non-rigid structure that can retain its shape and volume but that is not resistant to such change.

label.value: Single-dose Container

value.value: A container that holds a quantity of the preparation intended for total or partial use on one occasion only.

label.value: Skin Scarification Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a medicinal product by scratching the skin.

label.value: Solution and Suspension for Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution and suspension for suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled syringe. The solution and suspension are contained in different compartments of the pre-filled syringe, which contains all of the components necessary to prepare the suspension for injection.

label.value: Solution for Beehive Dispersion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a bee-hive dispersion.

label.value: Lodenosine

value.value: A nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor analog of adenosine. Lodenosine is a synthetic purine fluoro-dideoxyadenosine derivative that was rationally designed to have improved chemical and enzymatic stability. It has shown activity against clinical isolates and cell lines that are resistant to AZT, dideoxyinosine, and dideoxycytosine.

label.value: Polydactyl Stock, PF Forsthoefel Detroit U, 1973
Solution for Beehive Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a bee-hive solution.

label.value: Solution for Beehive Strip Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a bee-hive strip by application to an absorbent matrix; the bee-hive strip is usually used immediately after preparation.

label.value: Solution for Blood Fraction Modification Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in extracorporeal modification of a blood fraction that is returned to the patient following modification.

label.value: Solution for Cardioplegia Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended for use in inducing cardiac arrest during heart surgery. Some preparations may require mixing with other preparations prior to administration, for example to adjust the pH.

label.value: Solution for Cardioplegia/Organ Preservation Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution of electrolytes typically at a concentration close to the intracellular electrolyte composition, intended for inducing cardiac arrest during heart surgery, and for storage, protection and/or perfusion of mammalian body organs that are in particular destined for transplantation.

label.value: Solution for Dental Cement Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a dental cement.

label.value: Solution for Hemodiafiltration Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution containing electrolytes with a concentration close to the electrolytic composition of plasma, intended for parenteral use in hemodiafiltration. Glucose may be included.

label.value: Solution for Hemodialysis Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of an aqueous solution containing electrolytes with a concentration close to the electrolytic composition of plasma, intended for use in hemodialysis. Glucose may be included.

label.value: Solution for Hemodialysis/Hemofiltration Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as a solution for hemodialysis or a solution for hemofiltration.

label.value: Solution for Hemofiltration Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution containing electrolytes with a concentration close to the electrolytic composition of plasma, intended for parenteral use in hemofiltration. Glucose may be included.

label.value: PF Mouse
Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended to be introduced, usually in large volumes, usually into the circulating blood stream.

label.value: Solution for Infusion in Administration System Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for infusion presented in an administration system.

label.value: Solution for Infusion in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for infusion presented in a pre-filled syringe.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Administration System Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in an administration system.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Cartridge Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a cartridge.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Dose-Dispenser Cartridge Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a dose-dispenser cartridge.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Needle-Free Injector Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a needle-free injector.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Pre-filled Injector Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a pre-filled injector.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Pre-filled Pen Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a pre-filled pen.

label.value: Solution for Injection in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection presented in a pre-filled syringe.

label.value: JW MacArthur Stock, L Butler, 1949
Solution for Injection/Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for administration by injection or infusion.

label.value: Solution for Injection/Infusion in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a solution for injection/infusion presented in a pre-filled syringe.

label.value: Solution for Injection/Skin-prick Test Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution containing an allergen product intended for diagnostic use in a skin-prick test or as an injection (usually intraepidermal); it may also be licensed for immunotherapy treatment by injection (usually subcutaneous).

label.value: Solution for Intraocular Irrigation Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for irrigation of one or more internal structures of the eye, for example during surgical procedures.

label.value: Solution for Iontophoresis Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended for transdermal delivery by means of iontophoresis.

label.value: Solution for Organ Preservation Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution of electrolytes typically at a concentration close to the intracellular electrolyte composition, intended for storage, protection and/or perfusion of mammalian body organs that are in particular destined for transplantation.

label.value: Solution for Peritoneal Dialysis Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an aqueous solution containing electrolytes with a concentration close to the electrolytic composition of plasma and glucose in varying concentrations or other suitable osmotic agents, intended for intraperitoneal use as a dialysis solution.

label.value: Solution for Provocation Test Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution containing an allergen intended for provocation testing by the nasal, ocular or bronchial routes.

label.value: Solution for Sealant Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for the preparation of a sealant.

label.value: Solution for Skin-prick Test Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution containing an allergen product intended for diagnostic use in a skin-prick test.

label.value: PHH Mouse
Solution for Skin-scratch Test Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution containing an allergen product intended for diagnostic use in a skin-scratch test.

label.value: Solution for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a solution for infusion.

label.value: Solution for Solution for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use in the preparation of a solution for injection.
